<p>We now present a theorem due to Stefan Banach and Alfred Tarski (1924). =
The proof of this theorem uses the axiom of choice, in an essential manner,=
 to prove another counter-intuitive result. Some have claimed that this the=
orem thus refutes the axiom of choice. First, we identify some terminology.=
 In three-dimensional space, a <em>unit ball</em> is a set of points of dis=
tance less than or equal to <span class=3D"MathJax_Preview" style=3D"color:=
