<h2><a name=3D"H8"></a>8. Cohen=E2=80=99s Forcing Technique</h2>
<p>In 1963, the mathematician Paul Cohen introduced an extremely powerful m=
ethod, called forcing, for the construction of models of Zermelo-Fraenkel s=
et theory. A model M of set theory is a transitive collection of sets in wh=
ich the ZF (ZFC) axioms are all true, denoted by M <span class=3D"MathJax_P=
review" style=3D"color: inherit;"><span class=3D"MJXp-math" id=3D"MJXp-Span=
-3576"><span class=3D"MJXp-mo" id=3D"MJXp-Span-3577" style=3D"margin-left: =
