<p>Large cardinal axioms are statements that assert the existence of large =
cardinals. These axioms are widely viewed as being very promising new axiom=
s for set theory. Large cardinal axioms do not resolve the Continuum Hypoth=
esis but they have led mathematicians to formulate conditions under which C=
antor=E2=80=99s hypothesis is false (Woodin 2001, p. 688). As already menti=
oned, one cannot prove, in ZFC, that large cardinals exist. Yet, there is v=
ery strong evidence that their existence cannot be refuted in ZFC (Maddy 19=
88).</p>
